The paper deals with the problem of optimal placement of a jammer node in wireless localization systems, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of communication and information processing. The paper also involves networked systems and localization, which are relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the Cramer-Rao lower bounds, which are a fundamental concept in statistical inference and estimation, and therefore, the paper could be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
